# LandMap project rules

- Read `AGENTS.md` and `SKILL.md` before non-trivial changes.
- Everything is containerized. Use `make` targets (wrappers over
  `docker compose`); do not assume host-installed Python/Node.
- Stack is intentionally lightweight and self-hostable: React + Vite + MapLibre
  (frontend), FastAPI + PostGIS (backend), Caddy (proxy). No paid map providers
  or API tokens.
- Never commit secrets. Only `.env.example` is tracked; the stack must run with
  compose defaults and no `.env`.
- The API contract lives in `backend/app/schemas/`. Changing it requires
  updating the frontend client and e2e tests in the same change.
- Every behavior change needs tests: backend -> `backend/tests/unit/`,
  frontend -> `frontend/tests/unit/`, cross-stack flows -> `tests/e2e/`.
- Run `make lint` and `make test` before considering work done.
- Pin dependency versions; do not float to "latest".
